'''Obite Evan Ndicka''' (born 20 August 1999) is a professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Defender (association football)#Centre-back|centre-back]] for [[Serie A]] club [[AS Roma|Roma]]. Born in France, he plays for the [[Ivory Coast national football team|Ivory Coast national team]].

Ndicka is an academy graduate of [[AJ Auxerre|Auxerre]] and made his senior debut for the club in January 2017, aged 17. He spent the next season-and-half at the club, making 14 senior appearances before joining [[Bundesliga]] side [[Eintracht Frankfurt]] in July 2018.

==Early life==
Ndicka was born in [[Paris]] to a Cameroonian father and an Ivorian mother.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/FootballFicheJoueur62501.html |title=Obite Evan Ndicka |newspaper=L'Équipe |location=Paris |access-date=17 April 2021 |language=fr}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.lattaquant.com/voici-pourquoi-evan-ndicka-a-dit-oui-a-la-cote-divoire-et-non-au-cameroun/|title=Voici pourquoi Evan Ndicka a dit " oui " à la Côte d'Ivoire et " non " au Cameroun|date=June 7, 2023}}</ref>

==Club career==
===Auxerre===
Having joined [[Ligue 2]] side [[AJ Auxerre|Auxerre]] at the age of 13, Ndicka progressed through the club's academy and made his professional debut on 27 January 2017, starting in a 1–0 win over [[Clermont Foot|Clermont]].<ref name=Con>{{cite web|url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/Evan-ndicka-passe-professionnel-avec-auxerre/775462|title=Evan Ndicka passe professionnel avec Auxerre, Kenji-Van Boto prolonge|website=L'Equipe|date=5 February 2017|access-date=19 March 2017}}{{in lang|fr}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2017/01/27/france/ligue-2/clermont-foot-auvergne/association-de-la-jeunesse-auxerroise/2238021/|title=Clermont v Auxerre|website=Soccerway|date=27 January 2017|access-date=19 March 2017}}</ref> He signed his first professional contract with the club on 5 February.<ref name=Con/> He ultimately made 14 appearances for the club over the next season and half before signing for [[Bundesliga]] side [[Eintracht Frankfurt]] for a reported fee of €5.5m.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://thesefootballtimes.co/2019/03/07/the-eintracht-frankfurt-way-how-the-bundesliga-outfit-continue-to-punch-above-their-weight/₴|title=The Frankfurt Way: How the Bundesliga Outfit Continue to Punch Above their Weight|publisher=These Football Times|last=Billingham|first=Dan|date=7 March 2019|access-date=12 March 2019}}{{Dead link|date=January 2022 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>

===Eintracht Frankfurt===
On 5 July 2018, Ndicka signed for German club [[Eintracht Frankfurt]] on a five-year deal.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.goal.com/fr/news/officiel-evan-ndicka-quitte-auxerre-pour-leintracht/am3xmmujh7971ahodohutz5k5|title=Officiel - Evan N'Dicka quitte Auxerre pour l'Eintracht Francfort|trans-title=Official - Evan N'Dicka leaves Auxerre for Eintracht Frankfurt|publisher=Goal|last=Quarez|first=Benjamin|date=5 July 2018|access-date=5 July 2018|language=fr}}</ref> He quickly became an important member of the first-team squad and featured regularly for the club in the league and the [[UEFA Europa League|Europa League]].{{Citation needed|date=June 2023}} In February 2019, his performances earned him the Bundesliga Rookie of the Month award, a monthly title awarded to the highest performing under-23 player in a particular month, and saw him also nominated for the Rookie of the Season award.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.rookie-award.com/en/|title=Ndicka named Rookie of the Month|publisher=Bundesliga|access-date=12 March 2019|archive-date=28 May 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190528041919/https://www.rookie-award.com/en/|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/eintracht-frankfurt-defender-evan-ndicka-bundesliga-rookie-of-the-month-february-2019-2971|title=Eintracht Frankfurt defender Evan N'Dicka named Bundesliga Rookie of the Month|publisher=Bundesliga|date=12 March 2019|access-date=12 March 2019}}</ref> From then, he missed only one match for the remainder of the season as the club narrowly missed out on [[UEFA Champions League|Champions League]] qualification.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.rookie-award.com/en/|title=Bundesliga Rookie Award 2018/19 presented by Tag Heuer|publisher=Bundesliga|access-date=22 May 2019|archive-date=28 May 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190528041919/https://www.rookie-award.com/en/|url-status=dead}}</ref>

Having been a part of the side that won the [[2021–22 UEFA Europa League]],<ref name=":0">{{cite news |date=18 May 2022 |title=Frankfurt 1–1 Rangers (aet, Frankfurt win 5–4 on penalties): Trapp seals shoot-out success |website=[[UEFA]] |publisher=Union of European Football Associations |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefaeuropaleague/news/0275-152d4568b8fe-4c36a5db723e-1000/ |access-date=25 May 2022}}</ref><ref name=":1">{{cite web |date=18 May 2022 |title=Rangers suffer Europa League final shootout defeat to Eintracht Frankfurt |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2022/may/18/eintracht-frankfurt-rangers-europa-league-final-match-report |accessdate=20 May 2022 |work=The Guardian}}</ref> in June 2023 Ndicka officially left Eintracht after five seasons, following the expiration of his contract.<ref>{{Cite web |date=7 June 2023 |title=Eine Kante in der Abwehrkette |url=https://profis.eintracht.de/news/frankfurts-turm-in-der-abwehrkette-151081 |access-date=13 June 2023 |website=Eintracht Frankfurt |language=de-DE}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=7 June 2023 |title=Le défenseur Evan Ndicka quitte l'Eintracht Francfort |url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/Le-defenseur-evan-ndicka-quitte-l-eintracht-francfort/1401292 |access-date=13 June 2023 |website=L'Équipe |language=fr}}</ref>

===Roma ===
On 21 June 2023, Ndicka signed for [[Serie A]] club [[AS Roma|Roma]] on a five-year contract.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Evan Ndicka rejoint officiellement l'AS Rome et s'engage pour cinq ans |url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/Evan-ndicka-rejoint-officiellement-l-as-rome-et-s-engage-pour-cinq-ans/1404061 |access-date=22 June 2023 |date=21 June 2023 |website=[[L'Équipe]] |language=fr}}</ref> On 14 April 2024, during a match against [[Udinese Calcio|Udinese]] in the Serie A at the 73rd minute, Ndicka collapsed due to chest pain; he was eventually taken away on a stretcher, although conscious.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Burton |first1=Chris |title=Roma star Evan Ndicka collapses on pitch after feeling pain in chest as Udinese agree to abandon Serie A clash due to frightening incident |url=https://www.goal.com/en/lists/roma-evan-ndicka-collapses-pitch-pain-chest-udinese-agree-abandon-serie-a-clash-frightening-incident/blt4e9fcc4d8e9879a7#csc77903bcc3d0f841 |website=Goal.com |access-date=14 April 2024 |date=14 April 2024}}</ref> The match was abandoned fifteen minutes later with a 1–1 draw.<ref>{{cite web |title=Udinese v Roma match abandoned after Evan Ndicka collapses |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/68813346 |website=BBC Sport |publisher=BBC |access-date=14 April 2024 |date=14 April 2024}}</ref> The club stated later that Ndicka was conscious and taken to a hospital for "further checks".<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.reuters.com/sports/soccer/roma-defender-ndicka-collapses-pitch-with-match-suspended-2024-04-14/ |title=Roma's Ndicka in 'good spirits' after collapsing on the pitch |publisher=Reuters |date=15 April 2024 }}</ref>

On 28 November 2024, Ndicka scored his first goal for the club in a 2–2 away draw against [[Tottenham Hotspur F.C.|Tottenham Hotspur]] in the [[2024–25 UEFA Europa League|UEFA Europa League]].<ref>{{cite web |last=Kinsella |first=Nizaar |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/live/c207vdljp54t |title=Tottenham Hotspur 2–2 Roma |publisher=BBC Sport |date=28 November 2024 }}</ref> During the 2024–25 season, he became the first Roma outfield player since 2004 to play every minute of all 38 league matches without being substituted.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.asroma.com/en/news/73299/ndicka-becomes-first-roma-player-since-2004-to-play-38-matches-without-being-replaced |title=Ndicka becomes first Roma player since 2004 to play 38 matches without being replaced |publisher=AS Roma |date=26 May 2025 }}</ref>

==International career==
Ndicka represented France at [[France national under-16 football team|U16]] and [[France national under-17 football team|U17]] level and was called up to the [[France national under-18 football team|U18]] team for the first time by [[Manager (association football)|manager]] [[Bernard Diomède]] in March 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.larep.fr/malesherbois/sports/football/2016/02/10/lequipe-de-france-u17-se-rode-a-malesherbes-cet-apres-midi_11776641.html|title=L'équipe de France U17 se rôde à Malesherbes cet après-midi|website=La Republique du Centre|date=10 February 2016|access-date=19 March 2017}}{{in lang|fr}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://maligue2.fr/2017/03/14/quatre-jeunes-de-clubs-de-ligue-2-selectionnes-equipe-de-france-u18/|title=Quatre jeunes de clubs de Ligue 2 sélectionnés en équipe de France U18|website=MaLigue2|last=Dard|first=Philippe|date=14 March 2017|access-date=19 March 2017|archive-date=20 March 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170320143639/https://maligue2.fr/2017/03/14/quatre-jeunes-de-clubs-de-ligue-2-selectionnes-equipe-de-france-u18/|url-status=dead}}{{in lang|fr}}</ref> He then went on to play for every French youth squad up to the [[France national under-21 football team|Under-21 national team]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=17 May 2022 |title=Evan Ndicka, ce jeune Français révélé à l'Eintracht Francfort et qui va jouer la finale de la Ligue Europa |url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Article/Evan-ndicka-ce-jeune-francais-revele-a-l-eintracht-francfort-et-qui-va-jouer-la-finale-de-la-ligue-europa/1333366 |access-date=13 June 2023 |website=L'Équipe |language=fr-FR}}</ref>

In June 2023, he officially switched his allegiance to [[Ivory Coast national football team|Ivory Coast]],<ref>{{Cite web |date=8 June 2023 |title=Kessie called up for Ivory Coast national team duty amidst vacation plans |url=https://www.mundodeportivo.com/us/en/20230608/653352/kessie-called-up-for-ivory-coast-national-team-duty-amidst-vacation-plans.html |access-date=13 June 2023 |website=Mundo Deportivo USA}}</ref> subsequently receiving his first official call-up by the senior national team for the [[2023 Africa Cup of Nations qualification Group H|2023 Africa Cup of Nations qualification]] match against [[Zambia national football team|Zambia]];<ref>{{Cite web |date=6 June 2023 |title=Elim. CAN 2023 (5è j Zambie-Côte d'Ivoire) : Voici les 22 Eléphants sélectionnés |url=http://www.fifciv.com/?q=elim-can-2023-5%C3%A8-j-zambie-c%C3%B4te-d%E2%80%99ivoire-voici-les-22-el%C3%A9phants-s%C3%A9lectionn%C3%A9s |access-date=13 June 2023 |website=Ivorian Football Federation |language=fr}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=7 June 2023 |title=CAN 2023 : la liste de la Côte d'Ivoire avec Evan Ndicka |url=https://sportnewsafrica.com/breve/can-2023-la-liste-de-la-cote-divoire-avec-evan-ndicka/ |access-date=13 June 2023 |website=Sport News Africa |language=fr-FR}}</ref> however, he was eventually forced to withdraw from the squad, due to [[bureaucratic]] issues.<ref>{{Cite web |date=17 June 2023 |title=Jonathan Bamba va honorer sa première sélection avec la Côte d'Ivoire, Evan Ndicka pas encore |url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/Jonathan-bamba-va-honorer-sa-premiere-selection-avec-la-cote-d-ivoire-evan-ndicka-pas-encore/1403236 |access-date=18 June 2023 |website=L'Équipe |language=fr-FR}}</ref> He finally debuted with the Ivory Coast in a 1–0 [[2023 Africa Cup of Nations qualification]] win over [[Lesotho national football team|Lesotho]] on 9 September 2023.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.rti.info/depeches/2023/9/9/la-cote-divoire-bat-le-lesotho-sur-le-score-de-1-but-a-0-au-stade-laurent-pokou-de-san-pedro-le-but-ivoirien-a-ete-inscrit-par-ibrahim-sangare-a-la-16e-minute|title=La Côte d'Ivoire bat le Lesotho sur le score de 1 but à 0 au stade Laurent Pokou de San Pedro. Le but ivoirien a été inscrit par Ibrahim Sangaré à la 16e minute.|first=R. T. I.|last=Info|date=September 9, 2023|website=RTI Info}}</ref>

On 28 December 2023, he was selected from the list of 27 Ivorian players selected by [[Jean-Louis Gasset]] to compete in the [[2023 Africa Cup of Nations]].<ref>{{cite web|access-date=2023-12-29 |date=2023-12-28 |language=fr |last=Ouest-France |title=CAN 2024. La liste officielle de la Côte d'Ivoire pour la Coupe d'Afrique des Nations |url=https://www.ouest-france.fr/sport/football/equipe-cote-d-ivoire/can-2024-la-liste-officielle-de-la-cote-divoire-pour-la-coupe-dafrique-des-nations-42148136-a5c0-11ee-9c1f-9c2fef22f9fa |website=Ouest-France.fr}}<!-- auto-translated from French by Module:CS1 translator --></ref> On 11 February 2024, he won the [[2023 Africa Cup of Nations]] with the [[Ivory Coast]] with Coach [[Emerse Fae]].

Ndicka was included in the list of Ivorian players selected by coach [[Emerse Faé]] to participate in the [[2025 Africa Cup of Nations]].<ref>{{cite web|date=9 December 2025 |language=fr |title=Nicolas Pépé et Simon Adingra absents, Wilfried Zaha de retour : la liste de la Côte d'Ivoire pour la CAN |url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/Nicolas-pepe-et-simon-adingra-absents-wilfried-zaha-de-retour-la-liste-de-la-cote-d-ivoire-pour-la-can/1615689 |website=www.lequipe.fr}}<!-- auto-translated from French by Module:CS1 translator --></ref><ref>{{cite web|date=9 December 2025 |language=fr |title=CAN 2025: la liste de la Côte d'Ivoire, tenante du titre, avec le retour de Wilfried Zaha |url=https://www.rfi.fr/fr/afrique-foot/20251209-can-2025-la-liste-de-la-c%C3%B4te-d-ivoire-tenante-du-titre-avec-le-retour-de-wilfried-zaha |website=www.rfi.fr}}<!-- auto-translated from French by Module:CS1 translator --></ref>

On May 15, 2026, Ndicka was integrated by Ivory Coast coach [[Emerse Faé]] into his list of 26 players to compete in the [[2026 World Cup]].<ref>{{cite web|access-date=2 June 2026 |date=15 May 2026 |language=fr |title=La liste de la Côte d'Ivoire pour la Coupe du Monde 2026 |url=https://www.fifa.com/fr/articles/liste-cote-d-ivoire-coupe-du-monde-2026 |website=[[FIFA]]}}<!-- auto-translated from French by Module:CS1 translator --></ref>

